{"questionId":"13693417","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Mosaic Industries has <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn><mo> </mo><mi>EUR</mi></math> of fixed monthly operational costs. Additionally, Mosaic Industries must pay their phone case supplier <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mi>EUR</mi></math> for each case.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate Mosaic Industries’ average monthly profit if they sell each case at a price of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo> </mo><mi>EUR</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find total costs (both fixed and variable) <strong>AND</strong> subtract from their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>64</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>64</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>×</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br></strong><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find total profit from cases <strong>AND</strong> subtract fixed costs&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>16</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>×</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br></strong><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>14</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>EUR</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13693417","referenceCode":"23N.2.SL.TZ1.5d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate Mosaic Industries’ average monthly profit if they sell each case at a price of 16 EUR.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}